    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="906"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 P.W./12–944</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3213</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-09">December 9,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 28.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the Embassy’s
                    despatch No. 3091, October 24, 1944,<note n="33" xml:id="d906fn33">Not
                        printed.</note> in regard to the Far Eastern and Pacific Sub-commission of
                    the United Nations War Crimes Commission, and to report that an organizing
                    meeting of the Sub-commission was held at Chungking on November 28, 1944. Copies
                    of the minutes of the meeting have not yet been received; there is accordingly
                    enclosed a brief memorandum describing the action taken, together with copies of
                    pertinent documents which were distributed to the representatives at the
                        meeting.<note n="34" xml:id="d906fn34">Enclosures not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It will be noted that Dr. Wang Chung-hui was elected Chairman of the
                    Sub-commission; that Dr. P. H. Chang, Counselor of the Executive Yuan, was
                    elected Secretary General; that the British, Dutch and American representatives
                    were designated to form a Committee on Financial Arrangements; and that the
                    question of the date on which the war is considered to have begun in China,
                    raised by the Dutch and the Australians, is being referred to the Commission in
                        London.<note n="35" xml:id="d906fn35">For further information regarding the
                        organization, composition, and functioning of the Sub-Commission, see <hi
                            rend="italic">History of the United Nations War Crimes Commission</hi>,
                        pp. 129–131.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George Atcheson, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
